main event: A civilian observed a stationary object in the sky over Chicago, Illinois for 8-10 minutes on May 26, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as round with some flat sides, about the size of four planes.
The object had gray/white lights on the top, bottom and sides, but made no sound and left no trail or exhaust.
The object remained completely stationary during the 8-10 minute observation period.
The observer could not spot the object again when they went to look for it a second time.
The report includes two photographs of a similar-looking unidentified flying object that were taken in Albuquerque, New Mexico in June 1965.
sighted object: a stationary round object with flat sides and lights
photographs: no, but the report includes two photographs of a similar object from Albuquerque, NM
